{"title_page": "Sadollah Nasiri Gheydari", "text_new": "{{Infobox officeholder \n| native_name   = \n| name          = Sadollah Nasiri Gheydari\n| image         = Nasiri.JPG \n| order1        = President of [[Shahid Beheshti University]] \n| term_start1 = December 10, 2019<br>Acting: September 2, 2019 \u2013 December 10, 2019\n| term_end1 = \n| order2        = [[Islamic Consultative Assembly|Member of the Parliament of Iran]]\n| term_start2   = 28 May 2008\n| term_end2     = 28 May 2012\n| constituency2 = [[Zanjan and Tarom (electoral district)|Zanjan and Tarom]]\n| alongside2    = [[Jamshid Ansari]]\n| birth_date    = 1959\n| birth_place   = [[Qeydar]], [[Zanjan Province]], Iran\n| spouse        = \n| alma_mater    = [[Shiraz University]]\n| party         = [[National Trust Party (Iran)|National Trust Party]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://aftabnews.ir/vdcjaaeo.uqeyozsffu.html|title=\u0627\u0639\u0636\u0627\u06cc \u0634\u0648\u0631\u0627\u06cc \u0645\u0631\u06a9\u0632\u06cc \u062d\u0632\u0628 \u0627\u0639\u062a\u0645\u0627\u062f \u0645\u0644\u06cc \u0627\u0646\u062a\u062e\u0627\u0628 \u0634\u062f\u0646\u062f|language=Persian|publisher=Aftab News|accessdate=2 August 2016|date=27 September 2008}}</ref><br>[[Democracy Party (Iran)|Democracy Party]]<ref>{{citation|title=10 MPs joined Democracy Party|url=http://www.khabaronline.ir/detail/131142/Politics/parties|date=18 February 2011|access-date=23 August 2017|work=Khabaronline|language=Persian|id=472717}}</ref>\n}}\n'''Sadollah Nasiri Gheydari''' ({{lang-fa|\u0633\u0639\u062f\u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0646\u0635\u06cc\u0631\u06cc \u0642\u06cc\u062f\u0627\u0631\u06cc}}) is the current President of [[Shahid Beheshti University]] of Tehran. He is a [[physicist]] and [[professor]] at [[Shahid Beheshti University]], Iran.\n\nAfter obtaining his B.Sc in 1984, M.Sc in 1988 and Ph.D. in 1992 under [[Yousef Sobouti]], all from Shiraz University, he continued as associate professor in the Department of Physics of Shiraz University. In 1993, he was transferred to Zanjan University where he held various positions including head of its Department of Physics from 1994 to 1996, rector of its College of Science from 1996 to 1998 and again from 2002 to 2004, and vice-chancellor of education from 1998 to 2001.\n\nFrom 2002 to 2006, he was president of the [[Iranian Astronomical Society]] and was re-appointed in 2011.  In 2008, he was appointed vice president of the [[Iranian Physical Society]].\n\nGheydari's main research interests relate to [[asteroseismology|oscillations of stars]] in the presence of [[magnetic field]]s, [[quantum mechanics]] in [[phase space]], and [[Coronal heating problem|coronal heating]], as well as the selection of sites for optical [[observatory|observatories]].  His work has included a formulation of quantum mechanics in extended phase space ([[phase space]] in [[Position (vector)|position]] and [[momentum]] extended to include [[time]] and the value of the Hamiltonian as additional phase-space variables<ref>For an overview of extended phase space, see for ex. J\u00fcrgen Struckmeier: [http://www.gsi.de/beschleuniger/groups/FSY/veroeffentlichungen_berichte/theorie/extended_phasespace.pdf Hamiltonian mechanics in the \"extended\" phase space] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120331184547/http://www.gsi.de/beschleuniger/groups/FSY/veroeffentlichungen_berichte/theorie/extended_phasespace.pdf |date=2012-03-31 }}</ref>).\n\n== Selected publications ==\n* S. Khademi, S. Nasiri: ''Generalized [[gauge transformation]]s in phase space picture of quantum mechanics: Kirkwood representation'', Journal of Physics: Conference Series vol.&nbsp;128, no.&nbsp;1, 2008, 012016, {{doi|10.1088/1742-6596/128/1/012016}} ([http://iopscience.iop.org/1742-6596/128/1/012016/pdf/1742-6596_128_1_012016.pdf PDF])\n* Samira Bahrami, Sadolah Nasiri: ''Symmetry Transformation in Extended Phase Space: the Harmonic Oscillator in the Husimi Representation'', Symmetry Integrability and Geometry Methods and Applications (2008), vol.&nbsp;4, {{doi|10.3842/SIGMA.2008.014}} ([http://www.emis.de/journals/SIGMA/2008/014/ link]), [https://arxiv.org/abs/0802.0482 arXiv: 0802.0482]\n* S. Nasiri: ''[[Quantum potential]] and symmetries in extended phase space'', SIGMA 2 (2006), 062, [https://arxiv.org/abs/quant-ph/0511125 quant-ph/0511125]\n* S. Nasiri, S. Khademi, S. Bahrami, F. Taati: ''Generalized distribution functions in extended phase space''. In: V.K. Dobrev (ed.): ''Proceedings QST4'', Heron Press Sofia, 2006, vol.&nbsp;2, pp.&nbsp;820\u2013826\n* S. Nasiri, Y. Sobouti, F. Taati: ''Phase space quantum mechanics \u2013 direct'', Journal of Mathematical Phys. 47 (2006), 092106, [https://arxiv.org/abs/quant-ph/0605129 quant-ph/0605129]\n* S. Nasiri: ''Distribution functions on the light of uncertainty principle'', Jr. Sci. Tech., 29, A2, 259, 2005\n* S. Nasiri: ''Path integral approach to quantum state functions'', Jr. Sci. Tech., 4, 3, 1995\n* Y. Sobouti, S. Nasiri: ''A phase space formulation of quantum state functions'', International Journal of Modern Physics B, 7 (1993), pp.&nbsp;3255\u20133272\n* Sadollah Nasiri, Samira Bahrami: ''Reality of the [[Wigner quasiprobability distribution|Wigner Function]]s and Quantization'', Research Letters in Physics, vol.&nbsp;2009 (2009), article ID 298790, {{doi|10.1155/2009/298790}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://znu.ac.ir/modules.php?name=teachers&func=viewteacher&tid=352 Sadollah Nasiri Gheydari], University of Zanjan \u2013 [http://znu.ac.ir/modules.php?name=teachers&func=viewteacher&tid=352&abt=art papers], [http://znu.ac.ir/modules.php?name=teachers&func=viewteacher&tid=352&abt=EXPERIENCE background education], and [http://znu.ac.ir/modules.php?name=teachers&func=viewteacher&tid=352&abt=APPOINTMENT positions held]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nasiri Gheydari, Sadollah}}\n[[Category:Iranian Azerbaijani physicists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Zanjan, Iran]]\n[[Category:Iranian Azerbaijani politicians]]\n[[Category:Iranian Azerbaijani academics]]\n[[Category:National Trust Party (Iran) politicians]]\n[[Category:Deputies of Zanjan and Tarom]]\n[[Category:Iranian Shia Muslims]]\n[[Category:Ethnic Azerbaijani Shia Muslims]]\n[[Category:1959 births]]\n[[Category:Members of the 8th Islamic Consultative Assembly]]\n[[Category:Shiraz University alumni]]\n[[Category:Shiraz University faculty]]\n[[Category:Zanjan University faculty]]\n[[Category:Democracy Party (Iran) politicians]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Governor \n| native_name   = \n| name          = Sadollah Nasiri Gheydari\n| image         = Nasiri.JPG \n| order1        = President of [[Shahid Beheshti University]] \n| term_start1 = December 10, 2019<br>Acting: September 2, 2019 \u2013 December 10, 2019\n| term_end1 = \n| order2        = [[Islamic Consultative Assembly|Member of the Parliament of Iran]]\n| term_start2   = 28 May 2008\n| term_end2     = 28 May 2012\n| constituency2 = [[Zanjan and Tarom (electoral district)|Zanjan and Tarom]]\n| alongside2    = [[Jamshid Ansari]]\n| birth_date    = 1959\n| birth_place   = [[Qeydar]], [[Zanjan Province]], Iran\n| spouse        = \n| alma_mater    = [[Shiraz University]]\n| party         = [[National Trust Party (Iran)|National Trust Party]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://aftabnews.ir/vdcjaaeo.uqeyozsffu.html|title=\u0627\u0639\u0636\u0627\u06cc \u0634\u0648\u0631\u0627\u06cc \u0645\u0631\u06a9\u0632\u06cc \u062d\u0632\u0628 \u0627\u0639\u062a\u0645\u0627\u062f \u0645\u0644\u06cc \u0627\u0646\u062a\u062e\u0627\u0628 \u0634\u062f\u0646\u062f|language=Persian|publisher=Aftab News|accessdate=2 August 2016|date=27 September 2008}}</ref><br>[[Democracy Party (Iran)|Democracy Party]]<ref>{{citation|title=10 MPs joined Democracy Party|url=http://www.khabaronline.ir/detail/131142/Politics/parties|date=18 February 2011|access-date=23 August 2017|work=Khabaronline|language=Persian|id=472717}}</ref>\n}}\n'''Sadollah Nasiri Gheydari''' ({{lang-fa|\u0633\u0639\u062f\u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0646\u0635\u06cc\u0631\u06cc \u0642\u06cc\u062f\u0627\u0631\u06cc}}) is the current President of [[Shahid Beheshti University]] of Tehran. He is a [[physicist]] and [[professor]] at [[Shahid Beheshti University]], Iran.\n\nAfter obtaining his B.Sc in 1984, M.Sc in 1988 and Ph.D. in 1992 under [[Yousef Sobouti]], all from Shiraz University, he continued as associate professor in the Department of Physics of Shiraz University. In 1993, he was transferred to Zanjan University where he held various positions including head of its Department of Physics from 1994 to 1996, rector of its College of Science from 1996 to 1998 and again from 2002 to 2004, and vice-chancellor of education from 1998 to 2001. \n\nFrom 2002 to 2006, he was president of the [[Iranian Astronomical Society]] and was re-appointed in 2011.  In 2008, he was appointed vice president of the [[Iranian Physical Society]].\n\nGheydari's main research interests relate to [[asteroseismology|oscillations of stars]] in the presence of [[magnetic field]]s, [[quantum mechanics]] in [[phase space]], and [[corona]]l heating, as well as the selection of sites for optical [[observatory|observatories]].  His work has included a formulation of quantum mechanics in extended phase space ([[phase space]] in [[Position (vector)|position]] and [[momentum]] extended to include [[time]] and the value of the Hamiltonian as additional phase-space variables<ref>For an overview of extended phase space, see for ex. J\u00fcrgen Struckmeier: [http://www.gsi.de/beschleuniger/groups/FSY/veroeffentlichungen_berichte/theorie/extended_phasespace.pdf Hamiltonian mechanics in the \"extended\" phase space] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120331184547/http://www.gsi.de/beschleuniger/groups/FSY/veroeffentlichungen_berichte/theorie/extended_phasespace.pdf |date=2012-03-31 }}</ref>).\n\n== Selected publications ==\n* S. Khademi, S. Nasiri: ''Generalized [[gauge transformation]]s in phase space picture of quantum mechanics: Kirkwood representation'', Journal of Physics: Conference Series vol.&nbsp;128, no.&nbsp;1, 2008, 012016, {{doi|10.1088/1742-6596/128/1/012016}} ([http://iopscience.iop.org/1742-6596/128/1/012016/pdf/1742-6596_128_1_012016.pdf PDF])\n* Samira Bahrami, Sadolah Nasiri: ''Symmetry Transformation in Extended Phase Space: the Harmonic Oscillator in the Husimi Representation'', Symmetry Integrability and Geometry Methods and Applications (2008), vol.&nbsp;4, {{doi|10.3842/SIGMA.2008.014}} ([http://www.emis.de/journals/SIGMA/2008/014/ link]), [https://arxiv.org/abs/0802.0482 arXiv: 0802.0482]\n* S. Nasiri: ''[[Quantum potential]] and symmetries in extended phase space'', SIGMA 2 (2006), 062, [https://arxiv.org/abs/quant-ph/0511125 quant-ph/0511125]\n* S. Nasiri, S. Khademi, S. Bahrami, F. Taati: ''Generalized distribution functions in extended phase space''. In: V.K. Dobrev (ed.): ''Proceedings QST4'', Heron Press Sofia, 2006, vol.&nbsp;2, pp.&nbsp;820\u2013826\n* S. Nasiri, Y. Sobouti, F. Taati: ''Phase space quantum mechanics \u2013 direct'', Journal of Mathematical Phys. 47 (2006), 092106, [https://arxiv.org/abs/quant-ph/0605129 quant-ph/0605129]\n* S. Nasiri: ''Distribution functions on the light of uncertainty principle'', Jr. Sci. Tech., 29, A2, 259, 2005\n* S. Nasiri: ''Path integral approach to quantum state functions'', Jr. Sci. Tech., 4, 3, 1995\n* Y. Sobouti, S. Nasiri: ''A phase space formulation of quantum state functions'', International Journal of Modern Physics B, 7 (1993), pp.&nbsp;3255\u20133272\n* Sadollah Nasiri, Samira Bahrami: ''Reality of the [[Wigner quasiprobability distribution|Wigner Function]]s and Quantization'', Research Letters in Physics, vol.&nbsp;2009 (2009), article ID 298790, {{doi|10.1155/2009/298790}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://znu.ac.ir/modules.php?name=teachers&func=viewteacher&tid=352 Sadollah Nasiri Gheydari], University of Zanjan \u2013 [http://znu.ac.ir/module